news.title: Nagpur: Part OC first denied citing 14 flaws, NIT now overlooks nine flaws
news.para: On Tuesday and Wednesday, TOI had reported NIT demolished 35 shops without providing tenants copy of part OC, violated its own norms in building permit, went against its own deadline, did not give any hearing to tenants, and did not ensure tenants had got possession of new shops etc.

news.title: Indore: Five persons booked for developing illegal colony on government land
news.para: The accused have been identified as Amarchand, a resident of Simrol, Sumit Rajoriya, Kamal, Sandeep Bijoriya, and Punamchand - all residents of Asrawad Khurd.

news.title: WeWork turns profitable, reports around 40% year-on-year growth
news.para: The Bengaluru-based company, which started operations five years ago, reported an operating profit margin of Rs 25 crore for January-March, with around 40% year-on-year growth. The co-working operator reported revenue of Rs 800 crore for 2021.

news.title: Telangana plans two more recycling plants to handle construction waste
news.para: Only two units, each with 500 tonnes per day capacity, operate for construction waste whereas thousands of tonnes are produced every day, according to a report submitted by the Telangana government in National Green Tribunal on municipal solid waste management.

news.title: HC issues notice to Maharashtra real estate tribunal
news.para: The high court called for a response from the registrar of the Maharashtra Real Estate Appellate Tribunal and to consider whether matters arising from Goa can be heard by the Tribunal virtually.

news.title: Mumbai: Two weeks after FIR, society transfers membership to home buyer
news.para: Sengupta-Das, a 51-year-old widow and cancer survivor, had bought a 2BHK flat in the society for Rs 4.15 crore in February 2021, and moved in with her two children in July 2021.

news.title: Nagpur: HC disposes off plea after builder agrees to follow compromise pursis
news.para: Mohota had filed the petition challenging the April 29 notice issued by the Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT) directing him and 34 others to vacate their shops within three days.

news.title: Rajkot: Builder booked for forgery, cheating
news.para: Police booked Dhiren Dhorada after the Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) ordered the builder to pay Rs 1.28 crore to complainant Vipul Lodhiya with 9 per cent interest.

news.title: Pune civic body seals 59 rented municipal properties
news.para: Rajendra Muthe, the head of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC)'s establishments department, said, "The occupants of these properties did not pay the rent despite the civic administration asking them to clear the dues. So, the action has been taken. It will continue in the days to come."

news.title: SC asks Noida authority to pay Rs 100 crore to land owner in six weeks
news.para: The authority had argued in court that the plots Veerana had bought were in the middle of a commercial development hub and so the possession by him was illegal. The court ruled in favour of Veerana and restrained the authority from taking possession of the land.

news.title: Telangana government eyes Rs 3,000 crore from land & flat sales in two months
news.para: The auctions will be conducted by the Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority (HMDA) and Telangana State Industrial Infrastructure Corporation (TSIIC) in Rangareddy, Medchal and Sangareddy districts.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani Electricity disconnects power supply to Siddharth Colony as arrears mount over Rs 102 crore
news.para: Officials said that the power was disconnected from 8am to 5pm, but has been restored for certain hours on "humanitarian grounds" for essential purposes.

news.title: Panel set up to assess value of flats affected by partial collapse of Chintels Paradiso tower
news.para: A senior official said the owners of the seven flats which were affected by the collapse of a section of Tower D in Chintels Paradiso society have been given alternate flats of the same size in towers A and B.

news.title: Buyers can seek refund from first builder if redevelopment contract ended: MahaREAT
news.para: The first appeal was by Samudra Darshan Cooperative Housing Society in Andheri (W) against a November 2019 order of the MahaRERA, and the other two were against an August 2021 order in a review plea.

news.title: Special court extends builder Sanjay Chhabriaa's CBI remand till Friday
news.para: He was arrested on April 28 in a fraud case related with DHFL promoters — Kapil Wadhawan and Dheeraj Wadhawan — and former promoter of Yes Bank, Rana Kapoor.
